  "local_port": 60274,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets?",
  "response": "To obtain printouts of your past IRCTC journey tickets, you can follow these steps through the IRCTC website or mobile app. Ensure you use the same account credentials that you used to book the tickets initially.\n\n### **Using the IRCTC Website:**\n\n1. **Visit the IRCTC Website:**\n   - Go to [IRCTC's official website](https://www.irctc.co.in/).\n\n2. **Log In to Your Account:**\n   - Click on the **\"Login\"** button located at the top-right corner.\n   - Enter your **Username** and **Password**, then click **\"Sign In\"**.\n\n3. **Navigate to \"Booked Ticket History\":**\n   - Once logged in, hover over or click on **\"My Account\"** or **\"Booked Tickets\"** (the exact terminology may vary).\n   - Select **\"Booked Ticket History\"** from the dropdown menu.\n\n4. **View Your Past Bookings:**\n   - You'll see a list of all your past bookings. Locate the ticket you wish to print.\n   - Click on the **\"Print\"** icon or the specific journey details to view the ticket.\n\n5. **Print the Ticket:**\n   - Once the ticket details are open, use your browser's print function:\n     - Press `Ctrl + P` (Windows) or `Cmd + P` (Mac).\n     - Choose your printer or select **\"Save as PDF\"** if you wish to save it digitally.\n     - Click **\"Print\"** to finalize.\n\n### **Using the IRCTC Mobile App:**\n\n1. **Open the IRCTC App:**\n   - Launch the IRCTC Rail Connect app on your smartphone.\n\n2. **Log In to Your Account:**\n   - Enter your **Username** and **Password**, then tap **\"Login\"**.\n\n3. **Access \"My Bookings\":**\n   - Navigate to the **\"My Bookings\"** or **\"Booked Tickets\"** section, usually found on the home screen or in the menu.\n\n4. **Select the Desired Ticket:**\n   - Browse through your list of past journeys and select the ticket you want to print.\n\n5. **View and Share the Ticket:**\n   - Open the ticket details. You might have options to **\"Share\"** or **\"Download\"** the ticket.\n   - If you choose to share, you can send it to your email or another app from where you can print it.\n   - Alternatively, take a screenshot of the ticket and print it using your mobile's connected printer.\n\n### **Alternative Methods:**\n\n- **Email Confirmation:**\n  - Check the email account you used for booking the tickets. IRCTC typically sends a confirmation email with ticket details. You can print the ticket directly from your email.\n\n- **Contact IRCTC Support:**\n  - If you're unable to locate your past tickets through the website or app, consider reaching out to [IRCTC Customer Support](https://www.irctc.co.in/nget/contact-us) for assistance.\n\n- **Visit a Railway Reservation Counter:**\n  - As a last resort, you can visit any major railway reservation counter with a valid ID proof and request printouts of your past tickets. Provide necessary details like PNR number, travel date, and train information to facilitate the process.\n\n### **Tips:**\n\n- **Keep Your Credentials Safe:** Always ensure you're accessing your account from a secure device to protect your personal information.\n- **Regular Backups:** Consider saving or printing your tickets immediately after booking to avoid any hassle in the future.\n- **Update Contact Information:** Ensure your email and phone number are up-to-date in your IRCTC profile for seamless communication and ticket retrieval.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to retrieve and print your past IRCTC journey tickets without any issues.",
